## 6. Summary of Key Gender Inequality Effects on Children

| **Aspect**               | **Impact on Girls**                                                                 | **Impact on Boys**                                                               |
|--------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Education**            | Lower enrollment, early dropout, poor quality education, limited support           | Pressure to conform to masculinity, disengagement, shortage of male role models |
| **Health**               | Increased risk of child marriage, FGM, poor menstrual hygiene, limited healthcare  | Encouraged risky behaviors, higher injury and mortality rates                   |
| **Psychological Health** | Low self-esteem, depression, anxiety due to discrimination and violence            | Emotional suppression, aggression, higher mental health issues                  |
| **Social Development**   | Restricted social roles, caregiving burden, limited independence                   | Pressure to dominate, exclusion of others, homophobia                           |
| **Long-term Outcomes**   | Reduced economic participation, higher fertility, poorer child health outcomes     | Potential for involvement in violence, reduced educational attainment           |

